{"type": "root", "attrs": {"type": "node", "context": "dop", "icon": "COP2/xform", "internal": "snap_xform_ql", "version": "2", "namespace": "qLib"}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["Snap/Xform qL"], "extent": [45, 63]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": [{"type": "strong", "text": ["interface version 2"]}], "extent": [63, 87]}, {"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": ["Performs the transformations specified by previous ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/qLib::snap_point_ql::2", "type": "link", "text": ["Snap/Point qL"], "exists": true}, " SOPs."], "extent": [87, 199]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["This operator performs the snapping transformation(s) on the incoming geometry.\nThe geometry should have reference point(s) set up (see ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/qLib::snap_point_ql::2", "type": "link", "text": ["Snap/Point qL SOP"], "exists": true}, ")."], "extent": [199, 390]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Image", "value": "/nodes/sop/qLib--snap_xform_ql-2/snaptools_main.png", "type": "img", "text": ""}], "extent": [390, 425]}, {"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"type": "em", "text": ["Procedural snapping: red nodes specify a source position and up vector (based on the torus geo),\n  green ones set up target position, aim and up vectors (based on the grid).\n  Then a Snap/Xform qL SOP applies the transformation."]}], "extent": [425, 659]}], "container": true}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["Snapping is performed by specifying ", {"type": "em", "text": ["source"]}, " and ", {"type": "em", "text": ["target"]}, " point(s): the transformation will move the entire\ngeometry to have the source point(s) exactly match with the corresponding target point(s). The transformation\ncan involve translation (moving), rotation, and (uniform) scaling."], "extent": [659, 945]}, {"type": "tip_group", "body": [{"type": "tip", "indent": 0, "role": "item", "extent": [945, 950], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The transformation has two components:"], "extent": [950, 993]}, {"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": ["from source to world origin (", {"type": "q", "text": ["source-to-rest"]}, ")"], "extent": [993, 1046]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": ["from world origin to target (", {"type": "q", "text": ["rest-to-target"]}, ")\n    These can be done separately, allowing for additional work to be done to the geometry while it\u2019s\n    in the world origin position."], "extent": [1046, 1236]}], "container": true}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Snapping types"], "extent": [1236, 1257], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["The following snapping options are available, based on the number of points and/or vectors (directions)\nspecified."], "extent": [1257, 1374]}, {"type": "dt_group", "body": [{"type": "dt", "indent": 0, "text": ["Single point (point A)"], "extent": [1374, 1398], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Translate-only snapping."], "extent": [1398, 1428]}], "container": true}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 0, "text": ["Two points (points A/B; point A / aim direction)"], "extent": [1428, 1478], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Translation; rotation; uniform scale."], "extent": [1478, 1521]}], "container": true}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 0, "text": ["Three points (points A/B/C; point A/B and up vector; point A and aim/up vectors, etc.)"], "extent": [1521, 1609], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Translation; always-accurate rotation; uniform scale."], "extent": [1609, 1668]}], "container": true}], "container": true}]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Attributes"], "extent": [1668, 1685], "body": [{"t